message: 4. Mental health care is not a secret. The shame and stigma surrounding mental illness and addiction cause far too many people to suffer in silence and avoid seeking help. It‚Äôs time to change the conversation.

name: Kate Bolz
message: 3. Mental health care is a career. 94.6% of Nebraska‚Äôs counties have too few mental health professionals. We need to employ incentives like student loan relief to make our district an attractive place to study and work in mental health.

name: Kate Bolz
message: 2. Mental health care is for veterans. We need to undo the damage done to the VA by partisans like Jeff Fortenberry, and lower the rates of PTSD, addiction, and suicide among Nebraska‚Äôs veterans....

name: Kate Bolz
message:
I am running for Congress to fight for your health & wellbeing, which starts with addressing our nation‚Äôs mental health crisis. My 4 priorities for mental health:

1. Mental health care is health care. Any conversation must begin w/ a commitment to affordable health care for all.

name: Kate Bolz
message:
For people with and without histories of mental illness, these profound stressors have prompted episodes of depression, anxiety, OCD, substance abuse, eating disorders, and other challenges.

I recognize this as a public health emergency.

name: Kate Bolz
message: 2020 has been a perfect storm for our nation‚Äôs mental health. COVID raised feelings of fear & isolation; unemployment stripped many of health care & stability; social distancing separated us from loved ones & routines; tumultuous cultural & political climate isn't helping.

name: Kate Bolz
message:
On this #WorldMentalHealthDay, check in with a friend who might be struggling, or check in with yourself about your wellbeing and needs. Asking for help is a truly brave act.

As a trained social worker, the mental health of our communities matters to me.
